title: Space Pilot 3000
description: A pizza delivery boy named Fry awakens from a state of suspended animation and finds himself in a futuristic world populated by aliens, robots and spaceships.

title: The Series Has Landed
description: Fry eagerly anticipates his first visit to the moon...only to realize that it is home to a cheesy amusement park.

title: I, Roommate
description: Fry and Bender become a futuristic odd couple when they attempt to share an apartment.

title: Love's Labours Lost In Space
description: Leela finds herself the object of a starship captain's amorous advances.

title: Fear of a Bot Planet
description: Fry and Lela find themselves trapped on a planet ruled by human-hating robots.

title: A Fishful of Dollars
description: Fry discovers that a small amount of money left in his old bank account has accumulated into a fortune. But his nostalgia for all things 20th century puts him at odds with an evil oil tycoon.

title: My Three Suns
description: The crew visits a planet inhabited by liquid aliens. Fry, after delivering a package under the scorching heat of the planet's three suns, finds a bottle of cool blue liquid to quench his thirst. But when that liquid turns out to be the civilization's ruler, Fry finds he has become the new leader. Initially drunk with power, he soon discovers his life is in danger and must turn to his friends to help him dry out.

title: A Big Piece of Garbage
description: A gigantic ball of garbage carelessly launched off Earth in the 21st century returns on a collision course for New New York City and Fry and the crew set out on a mission to destroy it.

title: Hell Is Other Robots
description: Bender seeks religion after becoming addicted to electricity.

title: A Flight to Remember
description: Ep10 - As the Planet Express team vacations aboard the starship Titanic, the vessel falls victim to the gravitational pull of a black hole.

title: Mars University
description: Fry enrolls in Mars University, only to discover that his dorm roommate is a super intelligent monkey; Bender teaches a fraternity of robots how to be cool.

title: When Aliens Attack
description: Fry and his friends fight off an alien invasion of Earth by recreating a television drama from the 20th century featuring a sexily-attired single female lawyer.

title: Fry and the Slurm Factory
description: Fry wins a contest that takes the crew on a tour of the Slurm factory...and exposes its terrible secret.

title: I Second That Emotion
description: After Bender flushes Nibbler down a toilet, Fry, Leela and Bender journey through a sewer system inhabited by mutants.

title: Brannigan, Begin Again
description: After being court-martialed Zap Brannigan joins the Planet Express team...only to inspire Fry and Bender to mutiny against Leela.

title: A Head in the Polls
description: When the price of titanium skyrockets, Bender hocks his titanium-rich body to a pawnshop and lives the good life, until Richard Nixon s head uses the robot's torso to stage a political comeback.

title: Xmas Story
description: Fry and Leela find themselves targeted by a murderous robotic Santa Claus; Bender volunteers at a shelter for homeless robots.

title: Why Must I Be a Crustacean in Love
description: When Zoidberg runs amok during mating season, Fry sets out to teach him how to woo a mate.

title: Put Your Head on My Shoulders
description: Valentine’s Day turns into a nightmare for Fry after his head is surgically attached to Amy’s body.

title: The Lesser of Two Evils
description: Fry fears the worst when Bender's exact duplicate joins the crew on a mission to deliver a valuable atomic tiara to The Miss Universe pageant.

title: Raging Bender
description: Bender's popularity soars when he becomes a successful pro-wrestler, but when he is instructed to lose a fight, Leela steps into help him defeat an opponent trained by her old master.

title: A Bicyclops Built for Two
description: Leela finally encounters another member of her race, a handsome male. But when he turns out to be a jerk, she fears that leaving him will mean her species' extinction.

title: How Hermes Requisitioned His Groove Back
description: Hermes grows despondent when he misses an opportunity for a promotion; a female bureaucrat is turned-on by Fry's sloppiness.

title: A Clone of My Own
description: The Professor chooses his clone, Cubert, as the successor to his research...only to realize that Cubert has dreams of his own.

title: The Deep South
description: Deep beneath the ocean, the crew discovers the lost city of Atlantis where Fry falls hopelessly in love with mermaid.

title: Bender Gets Made
description: After joining the robot Mafia, Bender finds himself involved in scheme to loot the Planet Express spaceship of its cargo and destroy the crew.

title: The Problem With Popplers
description: Powerful alien beings threaten to devour of all mankind after the Planet Express crew inadvertently introduces earthlings to the aliens' tasty offspring.

title: Mother's Day
description: On Mother's Day, Mom unleashes hoard of rampaging robots to destroy the Earth-and only the Professor can stop them.

title: Anthology of Interest I
description: The Professor’s “What-If” machine simulates Bender, Leela and Fry’s wishes: Bender turns into a giant robot; Leela impulsively murders her friends; Vice President Al Gore, Stephen Hawking, Gary Gygax, and Nichelle Nichols come to the rescue when Fry inadvertently opens a rip in the space-time continuum.

title: The Honking
description: When Bender inherits a castle from his deceased uncle, he finds himself being pursued by a terrifying, driverless car.

title: War is the H-Word
description: Fry and Bender face off against an army of aliens on a far-off planet after they join the army to qualify for military discounts.

title: The Cryonic Woman
description: A woman from Fry's past unthaws in the year 3000, but when she feels out of place, she and Fry journey a thousand years into the future.

title: Parasites Lost
description: A miniature version of the Planet Express crew attempts to rid Fry's body of parasitic worms; meanwhile, Leela finds Fry's new personality irresistible.

title: Amazon Women in the Mood
description: Fry and the others find themselves trapped on a planet of Amazonian women ruled by a man-hating computer.

title: Bendless Love
description: Bender finds true romance with a coworker after crossing a picket line, but jealousy over his love's ex-boyfriend threatens to destroy everything.

title: The Day the Earth Stood Stupid
description: Only Fry can save Earth when evil brains from another world plot to make everyone stupid.

title: That's Lobstertainment!
description: Dr. Zoidberg promises his uncle-washed-up comedian Harold Zoid-that he will invest a million dollars in his Hollywood movie.

title: The Birdbot of Ice-Catraz
description: Leela fights to save the lives of penguins after the Planet Express ship is involved in an oil spill on Pluto.

title: The Luck of the Fryrish
description: Fry searches the ancient ruins of Old New York for his beloved lucky clover...only to conclude that his older brother stole not only the clover-but his life.

title: The Cyber House Rules
description: Tired of feeling like an outcast, Leela has a second eye grafted onto her face; Bender adopts twelve children after learning about the government's seemingly lucrative stipend.

title: Insane in the Mainframe
description: Fry and Bender become inadvertent participants in a bank robbery and are sentenced to a robot insane asylum where Fry comes to believe that he is indeed a robot.

title: Bendin' in the Wind
description: Bender is broken in a freak accident, but meets Beck who launches him on a singing career that turns him into a hero for other broken robots.

title: Time Keeps on Slipping
description: While creating a team of mutants to play the Harlem Globetrotters, the Professor accidentally causes a disruption in time that threatens the existence of the universe.

title: I Dated a Robot
description: Fry realizes a lifelong dream by dating a Lucy Liu robot.

title: Roswell That Ends Well
description: When the Planet Express ship travels through time to Roswell, New Mexico in 1947, Fry becomes his own progeny.

title: A Tale of Two Santas
description: As Christmas approaches...Bender faces execution when he fills in for the murderous Santa robot.

title: Anthology of Interest II
description: The What-If Machine tells Bender what it would be like if he were human, Fry what it would be like if life were like a video game, and Leela what it would be like if she found her true home.

title: Love & Rocket
description: As Valentine's Day approaches...Bender's romance with the Planet Express Ship puts the crew in jeopardy.

title: Leela's Homeworld
description: Leela finally learns the truth about her parents and her own identity.

title: Where the Buggalo Roam
description: Although Kif, Amy's boyfriend, retrieves her parents' buggalo herd and rescues Amy when she is kidnapped, they still refuse to accept him.

title: A Pharaoh to Remember
description: Bender's longing to be remembered motivates him to become a tyrannical Pharaoh on Osiris 4.

title: Godfellas
description: Bender accidentally gets shot out into the heavens and becomes god to a race of tiny aliens only to fail in that position and meet the Real Thing.

title: Future Stock
description: A cryogenically frozen 1980's guy is thawed, becomes the CEO of the failing Planet Express company, and threatens to have it acquired and gutted by it's largest competitor.

title: A Leela of Her Own
description: Leela believes she is a pioneer for women's athletics when she becomes the first female major league blernsball player.

title: 30 Percent Iron Chef
description: Bender learns to cook and competes against the pretentious, popular chef Elzar in an Iron Cook chef contest; Dr. Zoidberg is struck with remorse when he frames Fry for his own misdeed.

title: Where No Fan Has Gone Before
description: The Planet Express crew finds itself pitted against the cast of the original Star Trek when an energy creature seeks to determine who is more worthy of his fanatical devotion.

title: Crimes of the Hot
description: When the Earth is jeopardized by global warming, the crew attends a conference in Kyoto hosted by Al Gore's head. Richard Nixon's head attempts to rid the planet of robots -including Bender.

title: Jurassic Bark
description: Bender grows jealous when Fry attempts to clone his beloved fossilized dog.

title: The Route of All Evil
description: Hermes' and the Professor's sons try to outdo them in the business world but need their dads' help when success overwhelms them; Bender becomes a brewmiester.

title: A Taste of Freedom
description: In celebration of Freedom Day, Dr. Zoidberg eats the Earth flag, for which he is sentenced to death. In retaliation, the Decapodians enslave the entire world.

title: Kif Gets Knocked Up a Notch
description: When Kif gets pregnant,Amy questions her readiness to become a parent.

title: Less Than Hero
description: When Fry and Leela discover a mysterious cream that gives them unusual powers, they form a Superhero team along with Bender.

title: Teenage Mutant Leela's Hurdles
description: The Planet Express crew is exposed to a substance that causes everyone to revert to teenagers...and the Professor's attempt to correct the problem only makes thing worse.

title: The Why of Fry
description: Nibbler enlists Fry in a mission to blow up evil brains bent on destroying the universe; Fry time travels into the past to prevent himself from being cryogenically frozen.

title: The Sting
description: A killer bee sting sends Leela on a long, strange trip.

title: The Farnsworth Parabox
description: The Planet Express crew goes to a parallel universe made accessible by Professor Farnsworth's latest experiment.

title: Three Hundred Big Boys
description: When each Earthican receives a three hundred-dollar government refund, the Planet Express crew members pursue their respective dreams and desires.

title: Spanish Fry
description: S5, E12 When Fry succeeds in retrieving his nose, which was taken by aliens, a more precious appendage of his is placed in peril.

title: Bend Her
description: Bender's scam to win Olympic gold sets him on the road to becoming a celebrity wife.

title: Obsoletely Fabulous
description: A new model of robot threatens Bender, prompting him to go on a trip while upgrading his own technology.

title: Bender Should Not be Allowed on Television
description: Bender becomes a television star as well as a terrible role model for children.

title: The Devil's Hands Are Idle Playthings
description: Fry makes a deal with the Robot Devil so he can become a skillful musician and win Leela's heart.

title: Bender's Big Score - Part 1
description: Fry learns he has a tattoo of Bender that has universal consequences; Bender undergoes mind control by the new owners of Planet Express.

title: Bender's Big Score - Part 2
description: Bender and the new owners of Planet Express hatch a plan to steal ancient riches.

title: Bender's Big Score - Part 3
description: Fry discovers what his life could have been in the 20th century as things get progressively worse in the 30th.

title: Bender's Big Score - Part 4
description: Alien scammers buy the planet and banish its inhabitants to Neptune, leading to an intergalactic battle for Earth.

title: Beast With a Billion Backs - Part 1
description: Fry and the crew discover a giant hole in the universe and a seductive one-eyed tentacular alien on the other side.

title: The Beast with a Billion Backs - Part 2
description: Zap leads a military strike on the anomaly; a heartbroken Fry decides to leave the Universe; and Bender's obsession with the League of Robots bears fruit.

title: The Beast with a Billion Backs - Part 3
description: A tentacle creature from the Universe beyond the anomaly takes over our Universe; Leela, Amy, and Zap become the only resistance; and Bender becomes disillusioned with the League of Robots.

title: The Beast with a Billion Backs - Part 4
description: Everybody in the Universe and Yivo live together happily, except for a skeptical Leela; and Bender misses the humans, and commands a robot pirate ship to go get them back.

title: Bender's Game - Part 1
description: A rise in fuel prices coincides with the Planet Express crew's descent into a medieval, role-playing fantasy world.

title: Bender's Game - Part 2
description: Doctors order a robotomy when they can get through to Bender. Farnsworth, Leela, and Fry infiltrate Mom's dark-matter mine.

title: Bender's Game - Part 3
description: Farnsworth, Leela, and Fry wind up with Bender in his imaginary world of Dungeons and Dragons while Bender is getting a robotomy.

title: Bender's Game - Part 4
description: When Farnsworth and the gang reach Momon's Lair, an all-out battle ensues over the anti-crystal.

title: Into the Wild Green Yonder - Part 1
description: New Mars Vegas is built and Fry goes mad when he gains the power to read minds. Bender has an affair with the Donbot's showgirl-wife.

title: Into the Wild Green Yonder - Part 2
description: Fry learns more about his power and Leela joins the eco-feminists to stop Leo Wong from building a galactic mini-golf course.

title: Into the Wild Green Yonder - Part 3
description: Zapp, Kiff, and Bender try to capture the feministas. Fry secretly goes undercover working for Wong and learns about the Dark Ones and the Encyclopods.

title: Into the Wild Green Yonder - Part 4
description: Leela, Amy, and the Feministas are charged and stand trial for murder, mayhem, vandalism, kidnapping and resisting arrest.

title: Rebirth
description: After a devastating spaceship crash, the Professor attempts to resuscitate the crew with his birth machine.

title: In-A-Gadda-Da-Leela
description: Leela and Zapp Brannigan find themselves stranded on an Eden-like planet.

title: Attack of the Killer App
description: Fry gets carried away with social media and posts an embarrassing video of Leela online.

title: Proposition Infinity
description: Bender leads a campaign to legalize robosexual marriage (between humans and robots).

title: The Duh-Vinci Code
description: The crew races to future Rome to unearth the shocking secret of Leonardo da Vinci.

title: Lethal Inspection
description: Bender learns that he suffers from a mortal manufacturing defect.

title: The Late Philip J. Fry
description: The Professor invents a one-way time machine, but things go terribly wrong.

title: That Darn Katz!
description: Earth is invaded by a race of intelligent cats.

title: A Clockwork Origin
description: The theory of evolution is put to the test on a planet inhabited by robots.

title: The Prisoner of Benda
description: A revolutionary invention allows the crew members to exchange minds.

title: Lrrreconcilable Ndndifferences
description: Alien leader Lrrr faces a midlife crisis following a bungled Earth invasion.

title: The Mutants Are Revolting
description: Leela leads an army of underground mutants in a rebellion against the surface people.

title: Futurama Holiday Spectacular
description: The Planet Express crew learns the true meaning of X-mas, Robanukah, and Kwanzaa.

title: Neutopia
description: The crew members encounter a bizarre alien with the power to change their sexual characteristics.

title: Benderama
description: Bender gains the ability to replicate himself and threatens to overrun Earth with copies of himself.

title: Ghost in the Machines
description: Bender's disembodied software haunts the Planet Express building after he dies.

title: Law & Oracle
description: Fry quits his job and becomes a police officer assigned to the Future Crimes Division.

title: The Silence of the Clamps
description: After testifying against the Robot Mafia, Bender goes into hiding in the witness relocation program.

title: Yo Leela Leela
description: Leela becomes a Hollywood big shot after her series creation.

title: All the Presidents' Heads
description: The crew alters history when they travel back in time to the American Revolution.

title: Mobius Dick
description: Leela hunts down a mysterious four-dimensional space whale in the Bermuda Tetrahedron.

title: Fry Am the Egg Man
description: Fry's good intentions backfire when when he nurtures an alien egg that hatches into a monster.

title: The Tip of the Zoidberg
description: The crew uncovers a dark secret concerning a covert mission undertaken by the Professor and Dr. Zoidberg many years earlier.

title: Cold Warriors
description: Fry's sneezing reintroduces the common cold to the world of the future, with devastating consequences.

title: Overclockwise
description: When Bender increases his processing power, he becomes godlike.

title: Reincarnation
description: The series is reimagined in three distinct animation styles during the eighth season.

title: The Bots and the Bees
description: Bender fathers a child with the office soda machine.

title: A Farewell to Arms
description: An ancient prophecy predicts the world will end in the year 3012.

title: Decision 3012
description: Leela becomes campaign manager for a presidential candidate whose birth certificate is mysteriously missing.

title: The Thief of Baghead
description: Bender joins the paparazzi and attempts to photograph a famous actor whose face has never been seen.

title: Zapp Dingbat
description: Leela is horrified when her mother begins dating Zapp Brannigan.

title: The Butterjunk Effect
description: Amy and Leela become addicted to "Nectar", a nutritional supplement that boosts their performance in the future sport of Butterfly Derby.

title: The Six Million Dollar Mon
description: Fed up with his inferiority to machines, Hermes replaces his body parts with mighty mechanical upgrades.

title: Fun On a Bun
description: Fry is the victim of a horrific sausage-making accident.

title: Free Will Hunting
description: Bender embarks on a quest for the meaning of life after discovering that as a robot he lacks free will.

title: Near-Death Wish
description: The Professor is deeply disturbed when his parents return from virtual retirement aboard the Near-Death Star.

title: Viva Mars Vegas
description: The crew stages a casino heist to recover stolen property from the Robot Mafia.

title: 31st Century Fox
description: After saving a robotic fox from hunters, Bender becomes the hunted.

title: Naturama
description: Bender and the crew are re-imagined as wild animals in a nature documentary.

title: 2-D Blacktop
description: Professor Farnsworth joins a gang of street-racing punks.

title: Fry and Leela's Big Fling
description: Bender gains the ability to self-replicate, threatening to overrun Earth with vast swarms of copies of himself.

title: T.: The Terrestrial
description: After being marooned on a distant planet, Fry is befriended by a young monster.

title: Forty Percent Leadbelly
description: At a maximum security prison, Bender meets a famous folk singer and attempts to make a copy of his precious guitar.

title: The Inhuman Torch
description: Bender becomes a famous firefighter, but the crew suspects him of arson.

title: Saturday Morning Fun Pit
description: The Futurama gang stars in a trio of craptastic morning cartoons.

title: Calculon 2.0
description: The crew members alter history when they travel back in time to the American Revolution.

title: Assie Come Home
description: Leela becomes obsessed with hunting down a mysterious four-dimensional space whale.

title: Leela and the Genestalk
description: After a rare condition causes Leela to grow tentacles, she stumbles upon a secret genetic engineering facility.

title: Game of Tones
description: The crew uncovers a dark secret concerning a covert mission undertaken by the Professor and Dr. Zoidberg many years earlier.

title: Murder on the Planet Express
description: The crew becomes trapped aboard ship with a horrific alien creature.

title: Stench and Stenchibility
description: Dr. Zoidberg meets the love of his life while Bender squares off in a deadly tap dancing competition.

title: Meanwhile
description: Fry asks Leela to marry him, and they face their destiny together as the Professor's latest invention alters the fabric of time.
